#Approach:

Approach (Hinglish) – Capacity To Ship Packages Within D Days (Binary Search on Answer)

Is question mein hume ship ki minimum capacity find karni hai
aisi ki saare packages given order mein "days" ke andar ship ho jaayein.

Brute force mein hum har possible capacity check kar sakte hain,
lekin efficient solution ke liye Binary Search on Answer use karenge.

Key Idea:
Ship capacity ki range:
minimum capacity = max(weights)
maximum capacity = sum(weights)

Minimum capacity max(weights) kyu?
Kyuki ship ko kam se kam sabse heavy package uthana hi padega.
Usse kam capacity hui to wo package kabhi ship hi nahi hoga.

Maximum capacity sum(weights) kyu?
Kyuki agar ship ki capacity saare packages ke total sum ke equal ho,
to sab packages ek hi din mein ship ho sakte hain.

Agar kisi capacity "mid" par hum saare packages
days ya usse kam dinon mein ship kar pa rahe hain,
to ho sakta hai aur chhoti capacity bhi valid ho.
Isliye left side search karenge.

Agar kisi capacity "mid" par hume days se zyada din lag rahe hain,
to capacity chhoti hai,
isliye right side search karenge.

How helper works:
Helper batata hai ki given ship capacity "mid" par
saare packages ship karne mein kitne days lagenge.

Logic:
1. Packages ko given order mein hi load karna hai
2. Ek current day ka load maintain karo
3. Agar next package add karne se load capacity se exceed ho jaye,
   to naya day start karo
4. Naye day mein load = current package se start hoga
5. End mein total noOfDays return kar do

Example:
weights = [1,2,3,4,5], capacity = 5

Day 1 -> 1 + 2 = 3, next 3 add karenge to 6 ho jayega, so stop
Day 2 -> 3
Day 3 -> 4
Day 4 -> 5

Total days = 4

Steps:
1. low = max(weights)
2. high = sum(weights)

3. mid = (low + high) / 2

4. helper se calculate karo ki mid capacity par kitne days lagenge

5. Agar required days <= given days
   -> capacity valid hai
   -> aur minimum chahiye
   -> high = mid - 1

6. Else
   -> capacity kam hai
   -> bada capacity chahiye
   -> low = mid + 1

Loop ke end par low minimum valid capacity hoti hai.

Why return low?
Kyuki binary search ke baad low first aisi capacity hoti hai
jisme saare packages given days ke andar ship ho jaate hain.

Time Complexity:
maxi() -> O(n)
sumation() -> O(n)
helper() -> O(n)
Binary Search -> O(log(sum - max))
Total -> O(n * log(sum(weights) - max(weights)))

Space Complexity:
O(1)

One line intuition:
Aisi minimum ship capacity find karni hai jisse packages order maintain karte hue
days ke andar ship ho jaayein, isliye answer space par binary search lagate hain.

#Code:

class Solution {

    public int maxi(int[] arr){
        int n = arr.length;
        int maxVal = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            maxVal = Math.max(maxVal, arr[i]);
        }
        return maxVal;
    }

    public int sumation(int[] arr){
        int n = arr.length;
        int sum = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            sum += arr[i];
        }
        return sum;
    }

    public int helper(int[] arr, int mid){
        int n = arr.length;
        int noOfDays = 1;
        int load = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            if(load + arr[i] > mid){
                noOfDays++;
                load = arr[i];
            }
            else{
                load += arr[i];
            }
        }
        return noOfDays;
    }

    public int shipWithinDays(int[] weights, int days) {
        int low = maxi(weights);
        int high = sumation(weights);

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;
            int val = helper(weights, mid);

            if(val <= days){
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else{
                low = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return low;
    }
}
